news.title: Noida authority won't allow property brokers in office without passes
news.para: On June 15, OSD Avinash Tripathi issued a letter, saying that many people were found to be unnecessarily visiting various departments of the Authority.

news.title: Chandigarh: IT Park housing scheme of CHB awaits eco-clearance
news.para: The board applied for environmental clearance for the IT Park general housing scheme in February. It got approvals for structure, public health, electrical, town planning and architecture from departments concerned.

news.title: Ghaziabad: UP housing board to slash interest rate on dues of buyers
news.para: The move is expected to benefit homebuyers in Ghaziabad, where the Board is building a township in Sidharth Vihar and plans to construct another in Mandola.

news.title: Gurugram: Now, panel for structural audits of 60 societies
news.para: Consultants who fulfil the technical criteria set by the administration can apply by July 12. The panel of consultants is expected to be finalised by July 20.

news.title: ED arrests director of Mantri Developers in money laundering case
news.para: ​Sushil P Mantri was produced before a special Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) court in Bengaluru that sent him to the Enforcement Directorate custody for 10 days, it said in a statement.

news.title: NCDRC says slum-dwellers under rehab scheme are consumers
news.para: ​The commission upheld district forum and state commission orders that directed Hubtown Ltd to pay Rs 3 lakh compensation each to 30 complainants for delay in handing over the 225 sq feet tenements in Andheri (E).

news.title: Ahmedabad: 33% of builders use affidavit smokescreen
news.para: About 33% of the builders in Ahmedabad who are given building-use (BU) permissions for their multistoreyed buildings, taller than 25 metres, submit an affidavit to the civic body declaring that they will comply with fire safety rules.

news.title: Mumbai: Builder's bail rejected in cheating & forgery case
news.para: The 27 tenants of Satguru co-operative housing society in Kandivli had lodged a complaint against Tanna of Sai Tasveer Developers, who took up redevelopment of their building in 2010 but failed to complete it.

news.title: Bring all commercial & residential properties in Delhi under tax net: LG to MCD
news.para: ​In a review meeting on Friday, the LG also directed the Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD) to make all its services related to property tax filing, mutation and building plan sanction among others IT-enabled by July 31.

news.title: Complete TOD project before scheduled deadline: Delhi LG to DDA, NBCC
news.para: ​He had gone to take stock of the status and progress of work at the site of the project in east Delhi, according to the statement issued by the Raj Niwas.

news.title: Blackstone’s Nucleus Office Parks invests over Rs 100 crore in properties’ ESG upgrade
news.para: The operating platform houses 20 million sq ft office spaces across its 18 assets in top five property markets of the country including Mumbai, Bangalore, NCR, Chennai and Ahmedabad.

news.title: Indore civic body demolishes four dilapidated buildings
news.para: Officials concerned were instructed to identify and demolish old and dilapidated structures that could collapse during rainy season and lead to an accident, IMC deputy commissioner Lata Agrawal said.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM distributes rural residential rights documents to 11 lakh families
news.para: At a function organised in the auditorium of Lok Bhawan, Adityanath distributed the documents and stressed on making a self-reliant state.

news.title: Noida: RWA federation wants fees for property transfer to kin waived
news.para: The move comes after the state government on June 15 provided relief to property owners on transfer to blood relations for a fee of Rs 6,000, as against the 7% stamp registration duty earlier.

news.title: Ludhiana Improvement Trust asks Atal flat allottees to surrender extra allotment
news.para: LIT executive officer Kuljit Kaur said the allottees have to tender the affidavits on Rs 100 stamp paper duly attested by the magistrate that they did not get more than one flat to the names of their spouse and dependent children.
